H0.text: Lakes were formed by glaciers that flowed through the Ruby Mountain region in northeastern Nevada.

H1.text: Deserts were formed by glaciers that flowed through the Ruby Mountain region in northeastern Nevada.

H2.text: Volcanic necks were formed by glaciers that flowed through the Ruby Mountain region in northeastern Nevada.

H3.text: V-shaped valleys were formed by glaciers that flowed through the Ruby Mountain region in northeastern Nevada.

A4.text: Glaciers gouged out basins that are now alpine lakes.

A5.text: The central core of the range shows extensive evidence of glaciation during recent ice ages, including U-shaped canyons, moraines, hanging valleys, and steeply carved granite mountains, cliffs, and cirques.
